The paper deals with information theory and its applications to compressed sensing, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also discusses the polarization of the Renyi Information Dimension, which is a topic related to polar coding and channel polarization, making cs.ITP (Information Theory and Polar Coding) and cs.ITC (Information Theory and Channel Coding) also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions numerical simulations, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.MM (Machine Learning) or cs.LG (Machine Learning and Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories.
